# Step 4.2: Slack Integration - Environment Variables

## Slack Bot Token
# Get this from: https://api.slack.com/apps → Your App → OAuth & Permissions
# Required scopes: channels:history, channels:read, users:read, groups:history
AEP_SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-your-bot-token-here

## Slack App Token (optional, for Socket Mode)
# Only needed if using Slack Events API in the future
# AEP_SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-your-app-token-here

## Channels to Monitor
# Comma-separated list of channel names (without #)
AEP_SLACK_CHANNELS=eng-backend,eng-frontend,eng-sre,specimen-collection

## Example Usage
# After setting these variables, test with:
# curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/org/sync/slack \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{"user_id": "your-email@company.com", "channels": ["eng-backend"], "limit": 50}'
